1
00:00:00,540 --> 00:00:03,380
She said that back at the orphanage,
while they weren't very close,

2
00:00:03,380 --> 00:00:05,210
there was another girl about her age.

3
00:00:05,710 --> 00:00:08,280
- Really?
- Yes. And the necklace she wore...

4
00:00:08,650 --> 00:00:10,550
made it obvious
she came from a wealthy family.

5
00:00:11,220 --> 00:00:14,150
So she hoped to get a small reward
if the girl's parents ever showed up,

6
00:00:14,690 --> 00:00:16,690
and she apparently stuck to her
like a leech.

7
00:00:16,820 --> 00:00:20,360
- So, that girl...
- Yes, that's correct.

8
00:00:20,630 --> 00:00:22,290
And then what?

9
00:00:22,490 --> 00:00:25,600
The girl was a good student
and went on to high school,

10
00:00:26,500 --> 00:00:31,300
but the impostor quit middle school,
and they apparently lost touch after that.

11
00:00:34,040 --> 00:00:36,670
And there's one more crucial fact.

12
00:00:38,940 --> 00:00:41,210
The name Park Young Mi
that the impostor uses...

13
00:00:42,010 --> 00:00:43,480
isn't actually her real name.

14
00:00:44,380 --> 00:00:48,620
It was the name of the girl
with the necklace at the orphanage.

15
00:00:49,720 --> 00:00:50,720
What?

16
00:00:50,790 --> 00:00:54,230
When she registered for a resident ID,
she took the name Park Young Mi.

17
00:00:55,030 --> 00:00:56,130
Then that means...

18
00:00:57,030 --> 00:00:59,930
there's another Park Young Mi.

19
00:01:00,830 --> 00:01:01,830
Yes, sir.

20
00:01:02,870 --> 00:01:06,870
That other girl,
the one named Park Young Mi...

21
00:01:08,410 --> 00:01:10,110
could be my Eun Hye.

22
00:01:11,280 --> 00:01:13,080
Find her now!

23
00:01:13,380 --> 00:01:16,650
Scour the country for every Park Young Mi
if you have to.

24
00:01:17,080 --> 00:01:19,420
You must find my daughter, Eun Hye!

25
00:01:25,160 --> 00:01:28,090
Jung Suk Hee went by Park Young Mi
at the orphanage.

26
00:01:29,130 --> 00:01:30,160
What do I do?

27
00:01:30,730 --> 00:01:32,830
If they search for every Park Young Mi,

28
00:01:33,330 --> 00:01:35,930
it's only a matter of time
before they find Jung Suk Hee.

29
00:01:36,940 --> 00:01:40,070
This is driving me crazy.
What am I supposed to do?

30
00:01:40,070 --> 00:01:41,140
Darn it...

31
00:01:46,340 --> 00:01:48,780
The person you called is unavailable.
Connecting to voicemail.

32
00:01:48,980 --> 00:01:51,550
Lee Kang Hyuk, what are you doing?
Why aren't you answering your phone?

33
00:01:51,980 --> 00:01:53,220
Gosh, this is driving me nuts.

34
00:01:55,620 --> 00:01:58,390
Why can't it be me? Why?

35
00:01:58,790 --> 00:02:01,230
A pathetic weakling
like Kang Nam Bong is fine,

36
00:02:01,730 --> 00:02:02,760
but why...

37
00:02:04,860 --> 00:02:07,400
am I not good enough when I spent
my whole life living in your shadows?

38
00:02:09,200 --> 00:02:10,670
Looks like Lee Kang Hyuk is sulking.

39
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:12,800
He's so petty for a grown man.

40
00:02:23,920 --> 00:02:25,550
- Hello?
- Kang Hyuk.

41
00:02:26,650 --> 00:02:27,650
I'm hurting.

42
00:02:28,950 --> 00:02:30,790
It hurts so much I think I'm going to die.

43
00:02:31,820 --> 00:02:35,530
It hurts so much I can barely move.

44
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:37,400
Kang Hyuk.

45
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:40,600
Can you come over to my place right now?

46
00:02:40,970 --> 00:02:42,930
If you're in that much pain, call 911.

47
00:02:44,170 --> 00:02:45,700
You have family there, don't you?

48
00:02:47,570 --> 00:02:48,610
Kang Hyuk.

49
00:02:49,410 --> 00:02:52,280
You know very well I have no one but you.

50
00:02:53,780 --> 00:02:55,180
Of all the people in this house,

51
00:02:56,110 --> 00:02:58,620
who actually cares about me?

52
00:03:00,750 --> 00:03:01,750
Please?

53
00:03:02,620 --> 00:03:03,820
Kang Hyuk.

54
00:03:06,930 --> 00:03:07,930
All right.

55
00:03:08,530 --> 00:03:11,630
I'll head over and call you
when I'm there.

56
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:16,270
Lee Kang Hyuk.

57
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:18,500
You're in the palm of my hand.

58
00:03:19,040 --> 00:03:21,210
And where do you think you're going
with all that sulking?

59
00:03:27,610 --> 00:03:31,320
This audio file is practically
a confession from Chae Hwa Young,

60
00:03:31,780 --> 00:03:34,020
but we can't let her wriggle out of it
like last time.

61
00:03:34,220 --> 00:03:37,260
Let's gather more concrete evidence
and hit her with it all at once.

62
00:03:37,420 --> 00:03:38,460
We have to.

63
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:40,690
We can't let Chae Hwa Young get away
this time. Absolutely not.

64
00:03:41,130 --> 00:03:43,860
Last time, on top of her getting
Ssangkal to turn himself in,

65
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:46,930
Grandfather pulled some strings
beforehand, so we couldn't do anything.

66
00:03:47,470 --> 00:03:50,170
Because she's Seo Rin's mother,
and for the company's sake.

67
00:03:50,230 --> 00:03:52,540
But things are different now.

68
00:03:53,040 --> 00:03:56,310
Chae Hwa Young is no longer CEO,
and Chairman Ma is seeking his daughter.

69
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:59,040
If Grandfather finds his real daughter,

70
00:03:59,510 --> 00:04:01,450
he won't cover for Chae Hwa Young
this time.

71
00:04:01,910 --> 00:04:06,420
Then let's wait to release this evidence
until the Chairman finds his daughter.

72
00:04:06,780 --> 00:04:08,750
In the meantime, I'll look for the wrench.

73
00:04:09,150 --> 00:04:10,290
Chae Hwa Young, that evil witch.

74
00:04:10,920 --> 00:04:12,460
This time, I'll make sure
she's locked up for good.

75
00:04:29,810 --> 00:04:32,180
The necklace.
I have to find that necklace.

76
00:04:32,940 --> 00:04:35,310
There must be a definitive clue on it.

77
00:04:36,810 --> 00:04:37,850
Right...

78
00:04:46,590 --> 00:04:47,860
The inscription is missing.

79
00:04:48,630 --> 00:04:49,630
An inscription?

80
00:04:49,960 --> 00:04:51,000
She's not her.

81
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,700
Didn't he say there was an inscription?

82
00:05:06,940 --> 00:05:11,850
He clearly said there was no inscription.
So what inscription could he mean?

83
00:05:20,530 --> 00:05:21,530
(Large-print Bible)

84
00:05:27,170 --> 00:05:28,170
Found it!

85
00:05:40,410 --> 00:05:42,280
He said there was an inscription.

86
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:45,550
(Sil)

87
00:05:45,620 --> 00:05:46,620
Sil?

88
00:05:49,050 --> 00:05:51,120
If it's "Sil," as in Seong Sil?

89
00:05:52,990 --> 00:05:54,330
Then the other half must be...

90
00:05:54,860 --> 00:05:59,000
On the heart necklace, they had "Sil"
for my sister and "Chang" for her husband,

91
00:05:59,200 --> 00:06:01,970
and I heard they had them engraved
and each took a half.

92
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:04,940
Then that means the necklace
Jung Suk Hee has...

93
00:06:05,470 --> 00:06:08,440
must have "Chang"
from Ma Dae Chang's name on it.

94
00:06:31,530 --> 00:06:33,260
I didn't see you come downstairs.

95
00:06:33,770 --> 00:06:34,770
Where have you been?

96
00:06:35,270 --> 00:06:38,570
Where I was is none of your business.
How dare you!

97
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:39,940
Hey, why are you getting so mad?

98
00:06:40,300 --> 00:06:43,040
I just asked
because you popped up out of nowhere.

99
00:06:43,110 --> 00:06:45,240
Is it really something
to get so mad about?

100
00:06:45,310 --> 00:06:48,380
Forget it. I'm busy.
I don't have time to chat with you.

101
00:06:53,450 --> 00:06:56,950
(Ma Dae Chang)

102
00:07:16,610 --> 00:07:17,610
Kang Hyuk.

103
00:07:18,410 --> 00:07:19,510
I'm so cold.

104
00:07:20,610 --> 00:07:22,110
I'm starting to shiver.

105
00:07:26,380 --> 00:07:28,420
- Get in, quickly.
- Okay.

106
00:07:46,970 --> 00:07:47,970
Should we go to the emergency room?

107
00:07:51,380 --> 00:07:52,380
No, it's fine.

108
00:07:55,880 --> 00:07:58,020
I feel calmer just seeing you.

109
00:08:00,550 --> 00:08:01,820
What if someone sees us?

110
00:08:02,250 --> 00:08:03,320
Just for one minute.

111
00:08:03,860 --> 00:08:05,520
Just stay like this with me for a moment.

112
00:08:08,190 --> 00:08:09,590
You're the only medicine I need.

113
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:15,930
You don't feel like you have a fever.

114
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,000
Are you in a lot of pain?

115
00:08:20,910 --> 00:08:23,210
I was in unbearable pain earlier,

116
00:08:24,510 --> 00:08:26,340
but it's starting to go away
now that I'm with you.

117
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:34,620
Let's go somewhere we can talk.

118
00:08:48,900 --> 00:08:49,900
Park Young Mi?

119
00:08:50,470 --> 00:08:51,470
That's right.

120
00:08:52,470 --> 00:08:55,340
When Jung Suk Hee was at the orphanage,
her name was Park Young Mi.

121
00:08:55,970 --> 00:08:57,680
That imposter
who calls herself Park Young Mi...

122
00:08:58,110 --> 00:09:00,680
was following Jung Suk Hee around,
and when it was time to get her ID card,

123
00:09:01,010 --> 00:09:04,050
she apparently followed suit
and changed her name to Park Young Mi.

124
00:09:05,420 --> 00:09:08,120
You found out where
that fake Park Young Mi is staying, right?

125
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:10,120
Yes.

126
00:09:12,220 --> 00:09:13,220
Here.

127
00:09:14,260 --> 00:09:15,830
Get a copy of this necklace made, quickly.

128
00:09:16,460 --> 00:09:19,360
We're running out of time.
That old geezer, Chairman Ma,

129
00:09:19,930 --> 00:09:23,070
is checking every Park Young Mi nationwide
with a fine-tooth comb.

130
00:09:23,330 --> 00:09:26,400
Then he'll soon find Jung Suk Hee
as his real daughter.

131
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:29,570
We have to beat him to it.
If we're even one step behind,

132
00:09:29,970 --> 00:09:31,210
it's all over for us.

133
00:09:32,540 --> 00:09:33,540
What?

134
00:09:33,880 --> 00:09:35,650
You're saying
Chae Hwa Young came by the shop again?

135
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:40,280
- Chae Hwa Young is bad. She's a thief.
- What is Chae Hwa Young up to?

136
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:45,020
- Why does she keep coming to our shop?
- A man was here too.

137
00:09:45,520 --> 00:09:47,930
The man just dragged Chae Hwa Young
out of the shop.

138
00:09:48,190 --> 00:09:49,690
What? A man?

139
00:09:51,760 --> 00:09:56,030
- Mom, was he perhaps tall and young?
- Yes, he was.

140
00:09:56,300 --> 00:10:00,910
- The thief couldn't fight him off.
- He did?

141
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:02,710
It must have been Jun Ho.

142
00:10:03,510 --> 00:10:04,740
I wonder if he came to see you, Mom.

143
00:10:05,710 --> 00:10:06,810
To see Suk Hee?

144
00:10:08,250 --> 00:10:10,550
It's because we figured out
the secret of the hairpin.

145
00:10:29,100 --> 00:10:30,630
There's no need to try so hard,
Kang Baek Ho.

146
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:33,470
The outcome is already decided, anyway.

147
00:10:35,910 --> 00:10:38,010
It may look like
you'll marry Jang Mi now, right?

148
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:39,840
I was in your shoes.

149
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:43,350
You know a wedding can fall apart,
even on the wedding day.

150
00:10:43,410 --> 00:10:44,450
Don't get the wrong idea.

151
00:10:44,880 --> 00:10:46,680
We're married.
We're already husband and wife.

152
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:48,620
That's what makes me different
from you, Jun Ho.

153
00:10:52,590 --> 00:10:53,660
What do you think you're doing?

154
00:10:54,590 --> 00:10:55,730
I'm not your brother anymore.

155
00:10:56,660 --> 00:10:57,730
Stop acting like a spoiled brat.

156
00:10:58,060 --> 00:11:01,500
Don't compare your childish event
to a sacred marriage.

157
00:11:01,570 --> 00:11:04,340
I don't have a brother anymore.
I don't think of you as one either.

158
00:11:05,270 --> 00:11:06,600
You deceived me all this time.

159
00:11:06,970 --> 00:11:09,470
And I resent wasting my feelings
and energy on you.

160
00:11:10,210 --> 00:11:11,210
Perfect.

161
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:14,410
This should make it easier
for us to fight.

162
00:11:15,250 --> 00:11:17,310
You're just the bastard
who stole what was mine.

163
00:11:17,520 --> 00:11:19,920
Stole? Do you think Jang Mi is an object?

164
00:11:20,820 --> 00:11:24,220
And get this straight.
Jang Mi chose me of her own free will.

165
00:11:26,660 --> 00:11:28,790
We'll see about that.

166
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:32,630
Whatever happens from now on is on you,
so don't you dare complain.

167
00:11:33,330 --> 00:11:34,330
Got it?

168
00:11:46,880 --> 00:11:48,780
Oh my goodness! What happened in here?

169
00:11:50,150 --> 00:11:51,480
Baek Ho, who did this?

170
00:11:52,320 --> 00:11:54,050
I just saw Jun Ho leaving.

171
00:11:54,590 --> 00:11:55,850
Did Jun Ho do this?

172
00:12:01,390 --> 00:12:02,590
This is a real disaster.

173
00:12:02,930 --> 00:12:05,930
My gosh, they'll cause a scene at work.
What is wrong with those two?

174
00:12:10,970 --> 00:12:13,040
Is the necklace finished yet?

175
00:12:13,840 --> 00:12:15,170
Gosh, I'm a nervous wreck.

176
00:12:22,050 --> 00:12:25,520
The person you're calling is unavailable.
Connecting to voicemail.

177
00:12:25,580 --> 00:12:27,020
He's not answering. Again.

178
00:12:27,520 --> 00:12:29,420
After I primed him that much...

179
00:12:29,750 --> 00:12:31,020
Has he lost his mind?

180
00:12:32,760 --> 00:12:35,490
He should be waiting for my call.
What's gotten into him?

181
00:12:43,970 --> 00:12:46,500
Two iced Americanos and a slice
of strawberry shortcake, please.

182
00:12:46,570 --> 00:12:47,570
Okay.

183
00:12:47,870 --> 00:12:49,470
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

184
00:12:51,680 --> 00:12:53,280
I'll call your order number.

185
00:12:57,750 --> 00:12:59,880
Hello, this is Lee Kang Hyuk's phone.

186
00:13:01,820 --> 00:13:04,360
And who is this?

187
00:13:04,620 --> 00:13:06,320
It's Han Young Ja, Chae Hwa Young.

188
00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:09,190
One moment, I'll put him on.

189
00:13:10,560 --> 00:13:11,700
It's CEO Chae Hwa Young.

190
00:13:16,830 --> 00:13:18,670
- Yes, CEO Chae.
- What are you doing?

191
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:21,470
What are you doing with Han Young Ja
that she's the one answering your phone?

192
00:13:22,370 --> 00:13:23,370
Where are you?

193
00:13:23,710 --> 00:13:25,410
What is going on between you
and Han Young Ja?

194
00:13:25,710 --> 00:13:26,910
That's my personal life.

195
00:13:27,410 --> 00:13:28,480
Please stay out of it.

196
00:13:29,180 --> 00:13:32,580
Personal life? Hey, Lee Kang Hyuk.
Are you really doing this to me?

197
00:13:33,950 --> 00:13:36,850
- Let me know if you have instructions.
- Hey!

198
00:13:39,790 --> 00:13:40,790
Fine.

199
00:13:41,430 --> 00:13:42,830
I'll call you back later.

200
00:13:50,130 --> 00:13:51,140
I'm sorry.

201
00:13:51,700 --> 00:13:54,610
I've put you in a difficult position,
haven't I, Manager Lee?

202
00:13:55,740 --> 00:13:58,780
Not at all.
This was part of the plan, wasn't it?

203
00:13:59,110 --> 00:14:01,550
Order number 245 is ready.

204
00:14:02,910 --> 00:14:05,780
It's nice we ordered together,
so only one person has to go get it.

205
00:14:05,920 --> 00:14:08,250
- Just wait here a moment.
- No, I can get it.

206
00:14:08,320 --> 00:14:10,420
But you're the one who placed the order,
Manager Lee.

207
00:14:10,790 --> 00:14:11,790
Please, stay seated.

208
00:14:25,040 --> 00:14:27,470
So, he's with Kang Nam Bong's wife,
Han Young Ja.

209
00:14:28,570 --> 00:14:31,440
Is he flaunting her in my face, or what?

210
00:14:32,410 --> 00:14:34,910
Lee Kang Hyuk has gotten bold.

211
00:14:35,710 --> 00:14:38,020
So you're trying to prove you're a man,
is that it?

212
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:43,320
Chae Hwa Young, what's gotten into you?
Are you getting jealous?

213
00:14:44,920 --> 00:14:49,090
What's wrong with Chae Hwa Young?
What's got her so worked up?

214
00:14:49,730 --> 00:14:50,890
No, that's not it.

215
00:14:51,560 --> 00:14:54,430
Kang Hyuk must be doing this on purpose
because he's upset with me.

216
00:14:55,530 --> 00:14:58,440
There's no way he's with Han Young Ja.
Of course not.

217
00:14:59,100 --> 00:15:00,900
No matter what anyone says,
Kang Hyuk is my man.

218
00:15:07,040 --> 00:15:09,810
Kang Hyuk, you haven't forgotten
our promise, have you?

219
00:15:10,280 --> 00:15:11,280
See you later.

220
00:15:15,120 --> 00:15:16,120
Go on, have some.

221
00:15:16,750 --> 00:15:18,420
You have to get going soon, don't you?

222
00:15:19,760 --> 00:15:21,630
Yes, thank you.

223
00:15:21,860 --> 00:15:24,330
You always look after others, don't you?

224
00:15:25,130 --> 00:15:26,430
It's the nature of your job.

225
00:15:28,770 --> 00:15:29,930
But sometimes...

226
00:15:30,570 --> 00:15:32,400
you deserve to be taken care of, too.

227
00:15:34,610 --> 00:15:38,980
It seems like you have a really tough job,
Manager Lee.

228
00:15:39,680 --> 00:15:40,780
On the other hand,

229
00:15:41,550 --> 00:15:43,610
you're such a considerate person.

230
00:15:44,880 --> 00:15:46,320
Since you're a lawyer,

231
00:15:46,980 --> 00:15:49,590
I just figured
you'd be sophisticated and smart.

232
00:15:51,460 --> 00:15:54,020
That's only when I'm on the clock.

233
00:15:54,290 --> 00:15:55,730
When I was younger,

234
00:15:56,030 --> 00:15:59,460
I spent my youth nursing my son, Jun Ho,
through his illness,

235
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:01,030
and as I got older,

236
00:16:02,170 --> 00:16:04,700
I was busy supporting my kids
and their father,

237
00:16:05,670 --> 00:16:08,010
juggling work and housekeeping.

238
00:16:09,340 --> 00:16:10,940
I had no time for myself.

239
00:16:11,780 --> 00:16:14,450
- I see.
- Looking back on it,

240
00:16:14,910 --> 00:16:17,410
I wonder why I drained myself
living like that.

241
00:16:17,720 --> 00:16:18,980
I have so many regrets.

242
00:16:20,180 --> 00:16:23,190
I have nothing left, no reward,

243
00:16:24,020 --> 00:16:26,890
and I feel like
I just ran myself into the ground.

244
00:16:27,520 --> 00:16:28,530
I know what you mean.

245
00:16:30,660 --> 00:16:32,160
A life lived for others.

246
00:16:33,930 --> 00:16:38,300
At first, you think of it as devotion,
so you feel a sense of fulfillment,

247
00:16:39,740 --> 00:16:40,870
but when you look back,

248
00:16:42,810 --> 00:16:44,040
you wonder, "What did I even live for?"

249
00:16:46,410 --> 00:16:48,180
Sometimes you feel like an empty shell.

250
00:16:48,710 --> 00:16:51,450
Oh my, that's exactly how I feel.

251
00:16:54,750 --> 00:16:56,590
Looking at you, Manager Lee,

252
00:16:57,450 --> 00:16:59,660
it's like I'm looking in a mirror.

253
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:03,190
Plus, our tastes in everything, even food,

254
00:17:03,760 --> 00:17:04,930
are so similar.

255
00:17:07,030 --> 00:17:08,230
I mean...

256
00:17:09,270 --> 00:17:12,040
we're a funny pair, aren't we?

257
00:17:14,340 --> 00:17:18,640
That's the first time I've seen you smile,
Manager Lee.

258
00:17:20,810 --> 00:17:21,810
When you smile,

259
00:17:22,350 --> 00:17:23,810
you're quite charming, you know that?

260
00:17:24,450 --> 00:17:26,680
Well, I...

261
00:17:27,420 --> 00:17:28,490
I'm sorry,

262
00:17:29,120 --> 00:17:30,320
but I should really get going.

263
00:17:30,320 --> 00:17:32,390
Oh my, you do?

264
00:17:34,020 --> 00:17:35,030
What a shame.

265
00:17:35,990 --> 00:17:37,860
I felt like I'd just found
a fun friend to chat with.

266
00:17:40,530 --> 00:17:43,030
Please, just leave this and go on.

267
00:17:43,530 --> 00:17:44,640
I'll take care of it.

268
00:17:45,040 --> 00:17:46,070
No, I couldn't...

269
00:17:46,140 --> 00:17:49,910
Next time we meet,
you can clear the table, Manager Lee.

270
00:17:50,410 --> 00:17:51,410
Please, go ahead.

271
00:17:51,780 --> 00:17:52,780
All right.

272
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:54,480
Well then.

273
00:18:05,890 --> 00:18:06,890
Han Young Ja.

274
00:18:07,790 --> 00:18:09,060
What do you think you're doing?

275
00:18:30,310 --> 00:18:34,250
I'm Chae Hwa Young, CEO of Dream Hotel
and the Dream Group's daughter-in-law.

276
00:18:34,720 --> 00:18:38,960
The man you clumsily tried to con
happens to be my father-in-law.

277
00:18:39,220 --> 00:18:42,030
But, why did you want to see me?

278
00:18:45,930 --> 00:18:48,300
Don't tell me
you're going to press charges.

279
00:18:49,330 --> 00:18:53,200
Ma'am. I didn't do it on purpose.

280
00:18:53,800 --> 00:18:56,040
I really was not trying
to run some big scam.

281
00:18:56,110 --> 00:18:59,440
- I believe that much.
- I swear.

282
00:18:59,810 --> 00:19:03,150
I recalled she always
had a heart necklace as a kid,

283
00:19:03,850 --> 00:19:07,950
so I knew the Chairman would fall for it
if he saw one.

284
00:19:08,050 --> 00:19:10,550
Did you think so little
of Dream Group's intelligence...

285
00:19:10,850 --> 00:19:12,590
that such a cheap scam would work?

286
00:19:14,890 --> 00:19:18,530
But I called you here
because I have a question,

287
00:19:18,930 --> 00:19:21,570
- so don't be too scared.
- Pardon?

288
00:19:21,570 --> 00:19:24,970
You know all about
the real Park Young Mi, don't you?

289
00:19:25,970 --> 00:19:29,610
If my father-in-law finds out,
you're going straight to the police.

290
00:19:30,810 --> 00:19:33,310
So, I'll let it slide
if you just tell me everything.

291
00:19:34,180 --> 00:19:35,610
About what?

292
00:19:35,950 --> 00:19:38,650
Everything you know
about the real Park Young Mi.

293
00:19:39,220 --> 00:19:41,050
Every last detail.

294
00:19:41,550 --> 00:19:43,320
Don't leave a single thing out.

295
00:19:45,690 --> 00:19:47,320
Hello, Lawyer Bae.

296
00:19:48,030 --> 00:19:50,190
Yes, I'm doing fine.

297
00:19:50,390 --> 00:19:52,030
My wife?

298
00:19:53,600 --> 00:19:54,600
What?

299
00:19:55,700 --> 00:19:56,900
She took the day off?

300
00:19:58,240 --> 00:20:00,170
Okay, thanks. Bye.

301
00:20:03,510 --> 00:20:06,980
What in the world is that woman up to?

302
00:20:11,850 --> 00:20:14,950
Hey, didn't you say you were at work?

303
00:20:15,250 --> 00:20:17,790
When did I say that?
I said I had an errand to run.

304
00:20:18,920 --> 00:20:22,930
I heard you took the day off.
Where did you go dressed like that?

305
00:20:23,160 --> 00:20:25,930
I just told you, I was running errands.

306
00:20:26,460 --> 00:20:28,130
Are you the one having an affair?

307
00:20:28,430 --> 00:20:30,630
Well, an experienced cheater
can spot one right away.

308
00:20:31,670 --> 00:20:32,700
Perfect.

309
00:20:34,340 --> 00:20:38,640
So since we both have new partners,
let's make a clean break.

310
00:20:38,780 --> 00:20:40,510
You can enjoy your freedom too.

311
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:44,720
Then it's not an affair, is it?
It's just two single people dating.

312
00:20:45,520 --> 00:20:46,520
What?

313
00:20:47,180 --> 00:20:50,390
I've started to wonder
why married people...

314
00:20:50,650 --> 00:20:53,460
treat affairs like an addiction.

315
00:20:54,690 --> 00:20:58,030
It's hard to understand in theory,
so I decided to experience it firsthand.

316
00:21:00,360 --> 00:21:01,630
What is that supposed to mean?

317
00:21:02,330 --> 00:21:05,770
You're really going to see another man
without divorcing me?

318
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:10,470
After my experiment is over,
we can co-author a paper on it.

319
00:21:10,540 --> 00:21:13,280
Gosh, stop it.
I can only play along for so long.

320
00:21:13,510 --> 00:21:17,480
- You're just talking nonsense.
- We'll see if it's nonsense later.

321
00:21:17,880 --> 00:21:20,250
The royalties are split 50-50.
Don't you forget it.

322
00:21:20,350 --> 00:21:24,150
Then again, since I'm a lawyer,
you wouldn't dare try anything funny.

323
00:21:29,230 --> 00:21:30,930
What's gotten into her?

324
00:21:32,130 --> 00:21:33,130
That woman...

325
00:21:33,830 --> 00:21:34,870
Is she really...

326
00:21:36,300 --> 00:21:39,770
Go on. Tell me everything
about Miss Eun Hye.

327
00:21:40,540 --> 00:21:43,170
In the Chuncheon Orphanage records,
you'll see...

328
00:21:43,670 --> 00:21:47,510
that the girl wearing the heart necklace
was Park Young Mi.

329
00:21:48,410 --> 00:21:52,520
She was so bright that she went
to a college-prep high school,

330
00:21:52,580 --> 00:21:55,150
and since I dropped out,
we completely lost touch.

331
00:21:55,490 --> 00:21:57,290
Anything else distinctive about her?

332
00:21:58,120 --> 00:22:01,220
- Oh, right.
- What?

333
00:22:01,290 --> 00:22:04,930
Her hands
were always really sweaty and hot.

334
00:22:05,360 --> 00:22:07,660
So whenever she got nervous or flustered,

335
00:22:08,630 --> 00:22:09,630
like this,

336
00:22:09,900 --> 00:22:13,070
she had a habit of grabbing her ear.
She's done it forever.

337
00:22:13,640 --> 00:22:15,110
So Auntie was right.

338
00:22:15,470 --> 00:22:18,840
Is Young Mi really the daughter
of Dream Group's Chairman?

339
00:22:19,440 --> 00:22:21,310
- I could try and find out for you.
- What?

340
00:22:21,310 --> 00:22:22,750
About ten years ago, I think?

341
00:22:23,050 --> 00:22:25,420
I heard something about her
from another friend from the orphanage.

342
00:22:26,720 --> 00:22:28,250
I heard she was doing something.

343
00:22:35,990 --> 00:22:37,490
What's this?

344
00:22:37,890 --> 00:22:39,500
Don't go looking for anyone.

345
00:22:40,260 --> 00:22:41,670
That's your job now.

346
00:22:42,330 --> 00:22:45,640
And as for Park Young Mi,
she is not the Chairman's daughter.

347
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:47,600
Now that I hear it,
she is not the one at all.

348
00:22:48,670 --> 00:22:49,670
Really?

349
00:22:50,440 --> 00:22:52,280
Then this means...

350
00:22:54,280 --> 00:22:56,780
You’re to keep our meeting today a secret.

351
00:22:57,310 --> 00:22:59,880
And from now on, don't say a word
about Park Young Mi.

352
00:23:00,150 --> 00:23:01,150
Got it?

353
00:23:07,590 --> 00:23:08,660
Employee Chae Hwa Young.

354
00:23:09,560 --> 00:23:10,630
What are you doing here?

355
00:23:12,230 --> 00:23:15,600
What about you guys?
What are you two doing here?

356
00:23:15,970 --> 00:23:17,730
We're on a date, actually.

357
00:23:18,500 --> 00:23:19,700
You've got to be kidding me.

358
00:23:20,170 --> 00:23:22,810
Of all places to run into
Kang Baek Ho and Oh Jang Mi.

359
00:23:23,810 --> 00:23:27,540
If they find out I met Park Young Mi,
they'll know something's up.

360
00:23:29,010 --> 00:23:30,550
Oh my, ma'am...

361
00:23:30,910 --> 00:23:31,920
Let's go.

362
00:23:31,920 --> 00:23:34,180
You can drop me off home on the way.

363
00:23:34,680 --> 00:23:35,690
Who's that?

364
00:23:37,390 --> 00:23:40,420
Who? My guests left a while ago.

365
00:23:40,890 --> 00:23:43,060
If you're not coming,
I'm leaving without you.

366
00:23:46,260 --> 00:23:47,330
That's odd.

367
00:23:47,700 --> 00:23:49,270
I wonder who that was,
running off like that.

368
00:23:50,230 --> 00:23:51,230
I know.

369
00:24:00,610 --> 00:24:01,780
It's a pretty close match.

370
00:24:02,910 --> 00:24:06,820
But Jung Suk Hee's necklace is platinum
and shows its age up close.

371
00:24:07,480 --> 00:24:11,420
- This one is clearly just a copy.
- It is fake, so that makes sense.

372
00:24:12,220 --> 00:24:14,560
The "Chang" character looks the same
at first glance,

373
00:24:15,460 --> 00:24:16,890
but it is definitely a little different.

374
00:24:17,160 --> 00:24:18,730
Still, it should fool her for a while.

375
00:24:20,230 --> 00:24:21,330
Anyway, Kang Hyuk.

376
00:24:22,900 --> 00:24:24,730
Why did you meet with Han Young Ja?

377
00:24:26,740 --> 00:24:28,070
I'd rather not say.

378
00:24:29,170 --> 00:24:30,540
So it's a personal matter, is that it?

379
00:24:31,170 --> 00:24:32,180
Fine.

380
00:24:33,180 --> 00:24:34,280
But, Kang Hyuk,

381
00:24:35,180 --> 00:24:36,910
you know you're the only one
I have, right?

382
00:24:38,220 --> 00:24:40,650
But you have Professor Kang Nam Bong,
don't you?

383
00:24:42,950 --> 00:24:45,360
You have the wrong idea
about Professor Kang and me.

384
00:24:46,020 --> 00:24:48,190
How could you possibly compare him
to yourself?

385
00:24:49,130 --> 00:24:51,360
You and I go back more than 30 years.

386
00:24:51,830 --> 00:24:54,230
You're like my own flesh and blood,

387
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:57,030
another part of me. Don't you see?

388
00:25:01,500 --> 00:25:03,510
I know that you must have been hurt.

389
00:25:04,340 --> 00:25:05,810
About the harsh things I said last time...

390
00:25:06,610 --> 00:25:07,680
I apologize.

391
00:25:08,650 --> 00:25:09,650
I'm sorry.

392
00:25:11,250 --> 00:25:13,480
The people I hired for this
are professionals.

393
00:25:14,050 --> 00:25:15,050
Good.

394
00:25:15,650 --> 00:25:18,560
This plan for Jung Suk Hee can't fail.

395
00:25:18,820 --> 00:25:21,520
Yes. They say they've never failed before.

396
00:25:22,030 --> 00:25:23,030
You can trust them.

397
00:25:23,260 --> 00:25:25,600
We need to move fast.
Put the plan in motion.

398
00:25:26,300 --> 00:25:28,870
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

399
00:25:34,140 --> 00:25:37,870
Oh my, we're all out.
There's not much left today.

400
00:25:38,210 --> 00:25:40,180
Suk Hee is good with business.

401
00:25:40,880 --> 00:25:43,880
Looks like we're too late.
And the food here is so good.

402
00:25:44,480 --> 00:25:45,980
We made a special trip for this.

403
00:25:46,650 --> 00:25:50,020
- But you have basic side dishes here.
- Oh, right. I have these.

404
00:25:50,250 --> 00:25:51,250
Let me see...

405
00:25:53,420 --> 00:25:55,160
What's this one?

406
00:25:55,230 --> 00:25:58,730
That's stir-fried anchovies
in chili paste.

407
00:25:59,060 --> 00:26:02,500
- How do you make this?
- You have to give us the recipe!

408
00:26:02,830 --> 00:26:05,540
Suk Hee makes this really well.

409
00:26:08,940 --> 00:26:11,810
Oh no. What have I done?

410
00:26:11,880 --> 00:26:14,280
Oh my gosh. What do I do?

411
00:26:14,540 --> 00:26:18,850
Oh gosh, I'm so sorry.

412
00:26:18,850 --> 00:26:21,690
- It's all right. Don't worry about it.
- Right...

413
00:26:22,250 --> 00:26:23,290
Are you okay?

414
00:26:30,430 --> 00:26:32,130
(Chang)

415
00:26:34,230 --> 00:26:37,630
Oh, well. I guess we should just go.
We'll come back another time.

416
00:26:39,340 --> 00:26:41,600
Come again. Suk Hee's a great cook.

417
00:27:12,300 --> 00:27:15,510
(Chang)

418
00:27:31,960 --> 00:27:34,490
(Chang, Sil)

419
00:27:37,030 --> 00:27:38,290
"Chang."

420
00:27:38,290 --> 00:27:39,360
"Sil."

421
00:27:43,330 --> 00:27:46,000
(Chang, Sil)

422
00:27:46,970 --> 00:27:47,970
Oh my, Seo Rin!

423
00:27:50,910 --> 00:27:52,410
What is this?

424
00:27:53,210 --> 00:27:56,910
This is the necklace my grandfather gave
to his lost daughter, isn't it?

425
00:27:57,450 --> 00:27:59,780
Then why do you have both of them?

426
00:28:00,420 --> 00:28:02,450
No. It's nothing. Give it to me, Seo Rin.

427
00:28:05,920 --> 00:28:06,920
Wait, are you...

428
00:28:07,660 --> 00:28:09,360
Grandfather's daughter?

429
00:28:12,500 --> 00:28:13,500
Oh, shit!

430
00:28:40,860 --> 00:28:42,460
(The First Man)

431
00:28:42,690 --> 00:28:46,100
Are you that embarrassed to say it?
That we're dating?

432
00:28:46,460 --> 00:28:49,200
That jerk Lee Kang Hyuk.
If he betrays me, it's all over.

433
00:28:49,600 --> 00:28:52,700
You know that woman we saw the other day?

434
00:28:53,140 --> 00:28:58,040
She has my sister's habit.
My sister used to grab both of her ears.

435
00:28:58,510 --> 00:29:01,850
No matter what excuse she gives,
something about this doesn't add up.

436
00:29:02,450 --> 00:29:04,010
Mom must know something.

437
00:29:05,320 --> 00:29:07,320
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
